<div class="content">

  <!-- Summary -->
  <div class="summary-card">
    <p>At AiFloq, <strong>remote work isn't a perk — it's how we operate</strong>. We are a fully distributed team working asynchronously across time zones. There is no physical office, no mandatory login times, and no location requirement. Every team member is trusted to manage their own time and deliver results on their own terms. We believe the best work comes from people who have the autonomy to work in the way that suits them best.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- 3 Key Benefits -->
  <div class="benefits-grid">
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <span class="benefit-icon">🌍</span>
      <div class="benefit-title">Work From Anywhere</div>
      <div class="benefit-desc">No office, no commute, no geographic restriction. Work from home, a café, or anywhere in the world with a reliable internet connection.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <span class="benefit-icon">⏰</span>
      <div class="benefit-title">Flexible Hours</div>
      <div class="benefit-desc">No fixed 9-to-5. You own your schedule. Deliver your work on time and work during the hours when you're at your best.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="benefit-card">
      <span class="benefit-icon">💬</span>
      <div class="benefit-title">Async-First Culture</div>
      <div class="benefit-desc">We communicate asynchronously by default. No unnecessary meetings. Thoughtful written communication over constant real-time availability.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Policy Details -->
  <div class="section-heading">Our Remote Policy</div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">How We Work</div>
    <div class="section-title">Async-First, Results-Focused</div>
    <p>AiFloq operates on an async-first model. This means we default to written, asynchronous communication rather than real-time meetings. Updates, feedback, and collaboration happen through documented channels so every team member can work during their most productive hours — regardless of time zone.</p>
    <p>We do not measure productivity by hours logged or time online. We measure it by the quality and timeliness of the work delivered. Every team member is trusted as a professional to manage their own workload.</p>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>✅ <strong>What we care about:</strong> Did you deliver what you committed to, on time and to a high standard? That's the only metric that matters.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">Communication</div>
    <div class="section-title">Clear, Documented, Respectful</div>
    <p>All core communication happens in writing. This keeps everyone informed, creates a searchable record of decisions, and respects the time zones and schedules of every team member.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Primary channels:</strong> Email and messaging apps for day-to-day updates</li>
      <li><strong>Project updates:</strong> Documented in shared tools — not buried in chat threads</li>
      <li><strong>Video calls:</strong> Scheduled in advance, agenda-first, only when necessary</li>
      <li><strong>Response times:</strong> Within 24 hours on working days — no expectation of instant replies</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="tools-row">
      <span class="tool-chip">📧 Email</span>
      <span class="tool-chip">💬 Slack / Messaging</span>
      <span class="tool-chip">📋 Notion / Docs</span>
      <span class="tool-chip">📅 Google Calendar</span>
      <span class="tool-chip">🎥 Video calls (scheduled)</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">Working Hours</div>
    <div class="section-title">Flexible by Design</div>
    <p>There are no mandatory working hours at AiFloq. Team members work during the hours that suit their lifestyle, energy levels, and personal responsibilities. The only requirement is that agreed deadlines are met and communication is responded to within 24 hours on working days.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>No fixed start or end time — you define your working day</li>
      <li>Flexible around personal commitments, family, and lifestyle</li>
      <li>Overlap hours for collaboration arranged by mutual agreement</li>
      <li>Time zone differences are accommodated and respected</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">Equipment & Setup</div>
    <div class="section-title">Work With What Works For You</div>
    <p>AiFloq team members are responsible for their own workspace setup. We do not mandate specific equipment but we do expect a professional working environment that supports reliable output.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Stable internet connection sufficient for video calls and file sharing</li>
      <li>A device capable of running the tools required for your role</li>
      <li>A workspace where you can focus and communicate professionally</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For contracted roles and full-time engagements, equipment support and stipends may be available — discussed individually at the offer stage.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">Team Culture</div>
    <div class="section-title">Trust, Autonomy & Respect</div>
    <p>Remote work thrives on trust. AiFloq extends full trust to every team member to manage their time, communicate proactively, and deliver their best work. In return, we commit to clear expectations, prompt feedback, and a working relationship built on respect.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No micromanagement</strong> — you are trusted as a professional</li>
      <li><strong>Transparent expectations</strong> — scope and deadlines are clearly agreed upfront</li>
      <li><strong>Proactive communication</strong> — if something changes, we talk about it early</li>
      <li><strong>Respect for personal time</strong> — no pings outside agreed hours</li>
      <li><strong>Results celebrated</strong> — great work is acknowledged and rewarded</li>
    </ul>
    <div class="highlight-box">
      <p>🌍 <strong>We work with people from anywhere in the world.</strong> Location, time zone, background — none of these are barriers to being part of the AiFloq team. What matters is your skill, your communication, and your commitment to the work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="policy-section">
    <div class="section-label">Availability</div>
    <div class="section-title">Responsive, Not Always-On</div>
    <p>Being remote does not mean being available 24/7. AiFloq does not expect instant responses at all hours. We respect boundaries and personal time as a core part of our culture.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Team members set their own availability hours and communicate them clearly</li>
      <li>Emergency escalations are defined in project agreements — not assumed</li>
      <li>After-hours contact is by prior arrangement only</li>
      <li>Time off and personal days are respected without guilt or pressure</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <!-- Contact -->
  <div class="contact-box">
    <h3>Questions About Our Remote Policy?</h3>
    <p>If you're considering working with AiFloq and want to discuss our work structure, reach out — we're happy to answer any questions before you commit.</p>
